I"t<p>At a recent meeting of the World Economic Forum in Davos, HRH Prince of Wales delivered a <a href="https://www.princeofwales.gov.uk/speech/keynote-speech-delivered-hrh-prince-wales-world-economic-forum-davos-switzerland">keynote speech</a> about combating climate change. In the speech one statistic caught my attention: “With consumers controlling an estimated 60% of global G.D.P., people around the world have the power to drive the transformation to <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sustainable_markets">sustainable markets</a>.” As a consumer do I really have the power to change the world for the better?</p>
